schedule_summary: I prioritized high-traffic coverage and shift fairness, achieving a strong 0.24 Gini score to ensure hours are distributed equitably across your 50 staff members. To maintain this balance, I had to decline about 30% of individual preferences, resulting in five remaining gaps during specialized mid-week slots where availability was thinnest. I recommend cross-training two part-time servers for bar support or hiring one additional weekend closer to bridge these final coverage deficits.
